atization, in part because its leaders believe it would lead to China's "permanent decentering" in world history. As China's power increases, the party could begin restructuring global culture by inspiring actors in other Asian countries to uphold or restore authoritarian rule.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477947040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804779470423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804779470/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles